title: E-Team
description: The courageous investigators of Human Rights Watch's Emergencies Team risk their lives to document unlawful attacks on civilians by brutal dictators.

title: Edward VIII: The Nazi King
description: Using declassified FBI information, this documentary investigates the extent to which British King Edward VIII sympathized with the Nazis.

title: Einstein's Biggest Blunder
description: Einstein's Theory of Relativity holds that the speed of light is constant, but some cutting-edge scientists are questioning this fundamental premise.

title: Elaine Stritch: Shoot Me
description: Broadway legend Elaine Stritch looks back on her life and career in this portrait composed of candid reflections, archival footage and interviews.
actors: Elaine Stritch, Alec Baldwin, Tina Fey, James Gandolfini

title: Elephants: Spy in the Herd
description: Spy cams capture rarely seen elephant behavior, including two males battling for territory, a calf's birth, intra-herd jealousy and more.

title: Elizabeth at 90: A Family Tribute
description: A blend of the royal family's intimate recollections and rarely seen home movies pays tribute to Queen Elizabeth II on the eve of her 90th birthday.

title: Ella Brennan: Commanding the Table
description: Chefs, food critics and historians share stories about pioneering female restaurateur Ella Brennan, who put the New Orleans food scene on the map.

title: Elstree 1976
description: Then and now footage of bit players who appeared in "Star Wars" tells the story of how the film and its legions of fans changed their lives forever.
actors: Paul Blake, Jeremy Bulloch, John Chapman, Anthony Forrest

title: Empire Games
description: Interviews with scholars and dramatic reenactments bring to life the origins and history-making achievements of the world's greatest ancient empires.

title: End Day
description: A fictional scientist travels from London to New York experiencing a multitude of doomsday scenarios, about which various experts provide commentary.

title: End Game
description: Facing an inevitable outcome, terminally ill patients meet extraordinary medical practitioners seeking to change our approach to life and death.

title: Enlighten Us
description: This documentary digs deep to recount the saga of the superstar self-help guru convicted of negligent homicide in the deaths of three followers.

title: Escorts
description: Get an unflinching look at two high-priced call girls who rely on the internet to find clients, and the effects of their lifestyle on their families.

title: Expedition China
description: Cinematographers visit the remote forests and mountains of China in hopes of capturing footage of pandas, monkeys, red-crowned cranes and more.

title: Explained
description: This enlightening series from Vox digs into a wide range of topics such as the rise of cryptocurrency, why diets fail, and the wild world of K-pop.

title: Extraordinary: The Stan Romanek Story
description: Explore the life and times of Stan Romanek, who found himself in the middle of one of history's most intriguing stories of extraterrestrial contact.

title: Extreme Adventure Emergencies
description: Witness the treacherous obstacles that adventurers have encountered on a trans-Atlantic balloon flight, a solo mission to the North Pole and more.

title: Extreme Animal Attacks
description: In the wild or in captivity, animals can attack humans with devastating effect. Zoologist Nigel Marven examines some of the most unusual known cases.

title: Extreme Animal Obsessions
description: Meet people who are uniquely infatuated with animals -- from pet lovers who emulate their furry friends to chefs who harvest roadkill.

title: Extremis
description: Witness the wrenching emotions that accompany end-of-life decisions as doctors, patients and families in a hospital ICU face harrowing choices.
